comments.message:
It seems that vasync.pipeline passes an object of the following form:

{ operations: [], successes: [], ndone: 0, nerrors: 0 }

when going through an empty array of functions. Why would tryEach be different and pass "undefined" to its callback?

What I meant is why not have the following at line 576:

if (opts.args.impl === 'waterfall') {
     args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments, 2);
     res_key = 'results';
} else if opts.args.impl === 'tryEach') {
     args  = [];
     res_key = 'results';
}

and then here we could remove the special case for !== 'tryEach' and just call:

"nfunc.apply(null, args);"

in all cases, since next.bind(null, current) was already pushed into "args" above.

If you think it doesn't make the code clearer to understand, that's fine though.
